    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-08-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1270"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1270">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/2070.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">E. C. Bryan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Thank you for the offer. Say to the commander of troops in the Parral district
                    that he can not relieve himself from responsibility for acts of men under him.
                    He will be held personally responsible for whatever injury his soldiers inflict
                    upon Americans or other foreigners. It might be well to deliver this message in
                    the presence of two witnesses. Report names of commanders who received the
                    message, their replies textually and the names of witnesses who accompanied
                    you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
